parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle slows down or comes to a complete stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission oil leaks can cause fires, which can lead to serious injuries, damage to property, and even fatalities.
Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to property, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates when the brake pedal is pressed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine sludge can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The sudden activation of the engine fail-safe mode can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, increased stopping distance, and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: the steering and brakes lock up
the vehicle requires restarting to operate correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The breakage of spark plugs can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Spark plugs break off in the engine block
engine damage due to broken spark plug fragments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, resulting in loss of brake and power steering functionality, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine fail-safe mode warning light illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering vibration issue can cause driver discomfort, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vibration in the steering wheel when driving at speeds around 50 mph
vibration present from the first day of vehicle purchase.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper welding of the front strut can cause the strut to fail, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle drops to the ground
and the vibration can be felt throughout the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The abnormal vibration and suspension issues can cause a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: and the vibration can be felt throughout the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Proximity to Steering Column
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake line to the steering column can cause the brake line to wear out and fail, leading to brake failure, accidents, and property damage.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal to the accelerator pedal can cause inadvertent depression of the accelerator pedal when the brake is depressed, leading to accidents, property damage, and loss of control.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to accidents, property damage, and loss of control.
